{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/everything-about-pull-request/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"P`s Blog","author":"Princiya Sequeira"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e36c5395-c845-5d9c-8ad1-0a0d15dd161c","html":"<p>After learning <code class=\"language-text\">git</code> for the first time in 2015, I was expecting to contribute more to opensource.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/70d1f/expectation.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Pull request expectation\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/799d3/expectation.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/00d96/expectation.png 148w,\n/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/0b23c/expectation.png 295w,\n/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/799d3/expectation.png 590w,\n/static/ce1227d24bbab54cdede347dd51c9277/70d1f/expectation.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>But the reality turned out to be different.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/70d1f/reality.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Pull request reality\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/799d3/reality.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/00d96/reality.png 148w,\n/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/0b23c/reality.png 295w,\n/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/799d3/reality.png 590w,\n/static/60969b24baff09aa330bdda6643ad25b/70d1f/reality.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In this post, I will talk about the expectation and reality of opensource contributions from the perspective of the contributor, maintainer, and 7 tips on how to get them right.</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-first-time-opensource-contributor-experience\"><a href=\"#the-first-time-opensource-contributor-experience\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The first-time opensource contributor experience</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>My <a href=\"https://github.com/firefox-devtools/debugger/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Aprinciya+is%3Aclosed\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">first pull request</a> was to the Firefox devtools debugger project in February 2017.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>First time pull request contributions can be very intimidating, and so was the case with me. Hoping to land my first-time contribution, I started observing 2016’s Hacktoberbest. But I was lost with the plenty of opensource projects to choose from. In 2015, I had a <a href=\"../ace-your-outreachy-application/#not-every-attempt-is-successful\">first failed attempt</a>, but I was very determined in 2016. The entire October went with selecting projects until I settled down with the dev tools debugger project. It took another 3 months of observation into the project before I was confident of claiming the first issue. After the first pull request, I started to feel comfortable.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/70d1f/first-time.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Expectation vs Reality of first-time contribution\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/799d3/first-time.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/00d96/first-time.png 148w,\n/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/0b23c/first-time.png 295w,\n/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/799d3/first-time.png 590w,\n/static/aae1dffd51ca1b2e99e429372bedf61a/70d1f/first-time.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>The devtools debugger community did a great job of onboarding new contributors</li>\n<li>They had a good documentation</li>\n<li>The maintainers were available on slack for further questions and discussions</li>\n<li>Most important, they had a good code of conduct</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"tip-1\"><a href=\"#tip-1\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #1</h3>\n<p>When you are building an opensource community, appreciate your first-time contributors, encourage them, and offer pair-programming support.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tip-2\"><a href=\"#tip-2\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #2</h3>\n<p>Don’t treat any question as stupid. Remember, this can be the very first time that the contributor is even attempting to ask a question in a public forum.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Since the maintainers were very supportive, I ended up having a great first-time contribution experience.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"tip-3\"><a href=\"#tip-3\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #3</h3>\n<p>Avoid nit-picking for first-time contributors.</p>\n<p>Not everyone is a native English language speaker. Hence you can ignore the grammatical errors while naming variables or functions. Also, avoid using abbreviations as much as possible.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/70d1f/nit-pick.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Avoid nit-picking for first-time contribution\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/799d3/nit-pick.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/00d96/nit-pick.png 148w,\n/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/0b23c/nit-pick.png 295w,\n/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/799d3/nit-pick.png 590w,\n/static/57b3b2cba871dd684d264973f0c44555/70d1f/nit-pick.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<hr>\n<p>As for the horrible experience considered, my first nightmare was when someone commented on an issue I tried to help with a negative comment.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/d1c96/github.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 98.96507115135836%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Negative reaction received on Github\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/799d3/github.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/00d96/github.png 148w,\n/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/0b23c/github.png 295w,\n/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/799d3/github.png 590w,\n/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/2a3d6/github.png 885w,\n/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/ae92f/github.png 1180w,\n/static/66c4df0b98c827b680f65ca8247e29ce/d1c96/github.png 1546w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why do you still use this ugly hack instead of just installing xxxxxxxxxx?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What was bad about this comment, you may ask. Firstly, you cannot expect everyone to be at the same level as you in the opensource world. Obviously, I didn’t know why the person referred it to be a hack and using <code class=\"language-text\">ugly</code> alongside made it even worse.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tip-4\"><a href=\"#tip-4\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #4</h3>\n<p>Treat every contributor with respect.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tip-5\"><a href=\"#tip-5\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #5</h3>\n<p>When you offer to give suggestions, write an explanation why you think they are relevant. From the above example, it would have been very helpful for me to know what was hacky about my solution.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Another example I can recall of a bad experience is when I added <code class=\"language-text\">+1</code> to an already reported issue. I was a bit disappointed as to why the maintainer had downvoted my comment. I brought this point with another maintainer, and he explained why this was not a good practice.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/3ae72/bad-issue-example.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 57.66738660907127%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Example of a badly reported issue\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/799d3/bad-issue-example.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/00d96/bad-issue-example.png 148w,\n/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/0b23c/bad-issue-example.png 295w,\n/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/799d3/bad-issue-example.png 590w,\n/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/2a3d6/bad-issue-example.png 885w,\n/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/ae92f/bad-issue-example.png 1180w,\n/static/1c93440237c568558debc49eea58fc1f/3ae72/bad-issue-example.png 1852w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id=\"tip-6\"><a href=\"#tip-6\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #6</h3>\n<p>It helps a maintainer when you explain in detail. In the example above, what would have helped the maintainer was me being able to replicate the issue, write detailed steps, and help them debug the issue rather than write <code class=\"language-text\">+1</code> as a comment.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>The following incident happened to a repository I have been maintaining. There is no point venting your frustration in an issue comment unless you are offering to be helpful.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/fac82/lightbeam-bad-example.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; border: 1px solid #efefef max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 93.36550060313631%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Example of a bad comment for Lightbeam\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/799d3/lightbeam-bad-example.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/00d96/lightbeam-bad-example.png 148w,\n/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/0b23c/lightbeam-bad-example.png 295w,\n/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/799d3/lightbeam-bad-example.png 590w,\n/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/2a3d6/lightbeam-bad-example.png 885w,\n/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/ae92f/lightbeam-bad-example.png 1180w,\n/static/430272608116af395130a6a55f68da8a/fac82/lightbeam-bad-example.png 1658w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id=\"tip-7\"><a href=\"#tip-7\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tip #7</h3>\n<p>Treat maintainers with respect too. In general, keep all the comments respectful!</p>\n<p>Remember that most of the opensource contributions happen for free of cost. Be respectful of the contributors’ and maintainers’ blood, energy, and sweat.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Can you recall your first-time experience of creating a pull request or opening an issue to an opensource project? What is the one thing you can recall about what went well or a horrible experience you have had?</p>","timeToRead":4,"frontmatter":{"title":"7 tips to get your opensource contributions right","tags":["mentorship","opensource"],"date":"October 16, 2020","spoiler":"The good and the bad about opensource contributions","cta":"Opensource"},"fields":{"slug":"/everything-about-pull-request/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/everything-about-pull-request/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/tone-of-talking/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"tone-of-talking","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Tone of talking","tags":["draft"]}},"next":null,"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}